      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "For Kotliners: Kotlin doesn&#39;t have checked exceptions, so you cannot normally declare (in the function signature) that the function throws an exception. However, you can annotate the function with <code>Throws</code> annotation to make the compiler generate the same bytecode as declaring throws in the equivalent Java code. See [here] (<a href=\"https://kotlinlang.org/api/latest/jvm/stdlib/kotlin.jvm/-throws/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">kotlinlang.org/api/latest/jvm/stdlib/kotlin.jvm/-throws/&hellip;</a>) for more details."
    }, {
