    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>A workaround is to use a <a href=\"https://static.javadoc.io/org.mockito/mockito-core/2.13.0/org/mockito/stubbing/OngoingStubbing.html#thenAnswer-org.mockito.stubbing.Answer-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>willAnswer()</code></a> method. </p>\n\n<p>For example the following works (and doesn't throw a <code>MockitoException</code> but actually throws a checked <code>Exception</code> as required here) using <code>BDDMockito</code>: </p>\n\n<pre><code>given(someObj.someMethod(stringArg1)).willAnswer( invocation -&gt; { throw new Exception(\"abc msg\"); });\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The equivalent for plain Mockito would to use the <code>doAnswer</code> method</p>\n"
  }, {
